              <fr:mainmatter><html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\to  B]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000Y.xml" title="section-retraction pair" addr="forest://erct/erct-000Y" type="local">section</fr:link> of some <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[r\colon  B\to  A]]></fr:tex>; the type of <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000Y.xml" title="section-retraction pair" addr="forest://erct/erct-000Y" type="local">sections</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is, then, a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001I.xml" title="proposition" addr="forest://erct/erct-001I" type="local">proposition</fr:link>.</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="forest://erct/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>12</fr:month><fr:day>31</fr:day></fr:date><fr:addr>forest://erct/erct-002Q/0</fr:addr><fr:route>https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-002Q/0.xml</fr:route><fr:title text="sections of sections are unique › forest://erct/erct-002Q/0"><fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-002Q.xml" title="sections of sections are unique" addr="forest://erct/erct-002Q" type="local"><fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000Y.xml" title="section-retraction pair" addr="forest://erct/erct-000Y" type="local">sections</fr:link> of <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000Y.xml" title="section-retraction pair" addr="forest://erct/erct-000Y" type="local">sections</fr:link> are unique</fr:link> › forest://erct/erct-002Q/0</fr:title><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <html:p>Using the <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-0015.xml" title="the univalence principle for dependent functions" addr="forest://erct/erct-0015" type="local">univalence principle for dependent function spaces</fr:link>, we can see that the type of <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000Y.xml" title="section-retraction pair" addr="forest://erct/erct-000Y" type="local">sections</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\to  B]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-0025.xml" title="retract" addr="forest://erct/erct-0025" type="local">retract</fr:link> of the <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001Q.xml" title="fiber" addr="forest://erct/erct-001Q" type="local">fiber</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\circ  -]]></fr:tex> at <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[1_{B}]]></fr:tex>, using the <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-0023.xml" title="path object structure on sections" addr="forest://erct/erct-0023" type="local">univalence principle for sections</fr:link>.</html:p>

 <html:p>To show that the type of <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000Y.xml" title="section-retraction pair" addr="forest://erct/erct-000Y" type="local">sections</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001I.xml" title="proposition" addr="forest://erct/erct-001I" type="local">proposition</fr:link>, we may assume beforehand that we have such a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000Y.xml" title="section-retraction pair" addr="forest://erct/erct-000Y" type="local">section</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex>; therefore, because we have assumed a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000Y.xml" title="section-retraction pair" addr="forest://erct/erct-000Y" type="local">retraction</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> already, we know that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-000U.xml" title="biinverse" addr="forest://erct/erct-000U" type="local">biinvertible</fr:link> and <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-002N.xml" title="biinvertible maps are contractible" addr="forest://erct/erct-002N" type="local">therefore</fr:link> that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001T.xml" title="n-truncated map" addr="forest://erct/erct-001T" type="local">contractible</fr:link>. By <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-0026.xml" title="propositions are closed under retracts" addr="forest://erct/erct-0026" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="forest://erct/erct-0026" /></fr:link>, it suffices to show that the <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001Q.xml" title="fiber" addr="forest://erct/erct-001Q" type="local">fiber</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\circ  -]]></fr:tex> at <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[1_{B}]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001I.xml" title="proposition" addr="forest://erct/erct-001I" type="local">proposition</fr:link>, which follows via <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-001K.xml" title="contractible types are propositions" addr="forest://erct/erct-001K" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="forest://erct/erct-001K" /></fr:link> and <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/foreign/erct/erct-002O.xml" title="pushforward along biinvertible maps" addr="forest://erct/erct-002O" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="forest://erct/erct-002O" /></fr:link>.</html:p>
